Grafana Installation:
✅Go to - https://grafana.com/grafana/download

✅Run below command to install Grafana-server
sudo yum install -y https://dl.grafana.com/enterprise/release/grafana-enterprise-12.0.1-1.x86_64.rpm

✅Start and enable Grafana service
systemctl start grafana-server.service
systemctl status grafana-server.service
systemctl enable grafana-server.service
✅Main config file - /etc/grafana/grafana.ini
✅access Grafana via <Grafana server IP:3000>

✅Prerequisites
Datadog Account with:
API Key
Application Key
Grafana installed (cloud or self-hosted).
Datadog’s API endpoints:
https://api.datadoghq.com

✅On grafana server install below plugin
======================================
grafana-cli plugins install grafana-datadog-datasource
sudo systemctl restart grafana-server

In Grafana web console:
✅1.Go to Data Sources
✅2.Click Add data source
✅3.Select Datadog
✅4.Enter:
API Key – from Datadog
Application Key – from Datadog
API URL: https://api.datadoghq.com (default) or appropriate for your region
Optional: Site (datadoghq.com, datadoghq.eu, etc.)
✅5.Click Save & Test
